data.description: Welcome to Terracedale. This small subdivision is located close to town and within walking distance to Third Ward Park. This charming 1940s home is full brick, featuring beautiful hardwood floors in the large living room with a fireplace (gas logs), opening to a spacious dining room, with two bedrooms and two full baths. Off the living room, the former porch has been enclosed for a sunroom/office. The kitchen cabinets are white and have been updated, and the stainless steel gas stove/oven and refrigerator remain with the property. There is a dishwasher and a large entry area/drop-off zone/laundry area off the back with an additional storage closet. The bathrooms have tile floors, large tubs with shower combos, and were updated in the last 10 years. In the back, you have a brick terrace and a large storage building. Do not miss this home—make it your own.
